title: SFH on supply of powdered formula and vaccination programmes
content_text:
p>
	Following is the transcript of remarks made by the Secretary for Food and 
	Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, after attending a public function this morning 
	(November 21): Reporter: (About the report on the stress test on the supply of infant 
	formula.) Secretary for Food and Health: Under the steer of the Committee on Supply 
	Chain of Powdered Formula and with the assistance of a consultant company, 
	we conducted a stress test covering the period before (and after) the Golden

we conducted a stress test covering the period before (and after) the Golden 
	Week in early October. The report was yesterday tabled to the committee, 
	which consists of representatives from the relevant industry, the retail 
	business and consumers. In the nutshell, there were still inadequacies in 
	our supply chain of formula milk. (Members of) the committee agree to work 
	continuously to improve the supply chain. Reporter: There are allegations that local parents still could not get 
	infant formula. How will the Government work with the retail sector to help

infant formula. How will the Government work with the retail sector to help 
	these parents? Secretary for Food and Health: The Government is concerned about reports 
	that there is still a shortage of powdered formula supply in the market even 
	outside the Golden Week. In this regard, the committee has agreed to 
	continue its work to improve the supply arrangement at the retail end. Reporter: (On the supply of powdered formula.) Secretary for Food and Health: It will be (a piece of) continuous work for

the committee. Reporter: A 3-year old boy has died of pneumococcal infection. Now the Hong 
	Kong Medical Association says that the Government should extend its free 
	vaccination programme to cover children up to 3 years old. Would you 
	consider that? Secretary for Food and Health: The Government is under the advice of an 
	expert committee on vaccination programmes. Any matter related to the 
	application of vaccination programmes in the prevention of infectious 
	diseases will be considered by this expert committee. (Please also refer to the
diseases will be considered by this expert committee. (Please also refer to the Chinese portion of the transcript.)
